point for the most\npart. A few posted plus signs.\nThe decline was general, af\nfecting steels, motors, rails,\nchemicals, oils and most air\ncrafts. Utilities, after showing\nan early bulge to the upside,\nretreated mildly. Radio-televi\nsions and distillers showed a\nnaiTowly mixed price trend.\nSome profit talcing was In\norder after the market's sus\ntained rise of more than a\nweek. Pre-week-end caution\nwas apparent.\nThe news brought no relief\nto the picture of recession.\nGovernment reports forecast\nsizable cutbacks in spending\nboth by businessmen and con-;\nsumers this year.\nThe Associated Press average\nof 60 stocks at noon was down\nSO cents to $163.50 with the\nindustrials down to 70 cents,\nthe rails down 60 cents and the\nutilities down 10 cents.\nCorporate bonds were mixed.\nUnited States Governments\nrose moderately.\nRambler Car Sales\nJump in 10 Days\nDETROIT. Mar. 15 <j\u00abP).\nAmerican Motors retailers sold\n3,779 Rambler cars in the first\n10 days of March, the company\nreported today. Sales in the\nlike 1957 period numbered 2.048:\nunits.\nFor the model year (starting\nOctober 1) to date Rambler\nsales total 51,829 cars against\n31,133 for the like period of\nthe 1957 model year.\nD. C. SECURITIES\nSALES\nFot Elec Pwr com\u2014:i(> tt 2t J g. 1(KI\nat '24+. 30 at 241\u00bb. 200 at 24',\u00ab.\n100 at 24y*.\nWash Gag Lt com\u2014l 3 at 38+. 80 at\n08*. 200 at 38 V*.\nBONDS Bid Asked\nGeorgetown Gag 1 5s 61 lul 104\nNatl Mortaage 6*s bl. 5*\nPot Elec Pwr a+a 77 85\nPot Elec Pwr as 8a 82\nPot Elec Pwr 2+a 84 72\nTer RI&W Cp l\u00bbt 4s 58 08\nWashington Gas At 8U 100\nPUBLIC UTILITY STOCKS\nAmer Tel Tel 0 giro*\nPot Elec Pwr 1.20 x 24 24*\nPepco 2.44'i of 2.44 40* M\nPot Elec Pwr 2.48 246 So A1\nWash Oat Lt 2 37* 38*\nWash Gas L cm pf 4.25 85 87\nWash GLcucv pf 4.50 128\nBANKS AND TRUST COMPANIES\nBank of Bethesda 2 .86\nBank .of commerce tlO. 330\nCapital 11 28\nLincoln tl 70\nNatl Say Tr 1.60 79 85\nRifts ta.eo 127 132\nSuburban Trust 1.5